OL,3,CFood inflation jumps to 18-month high
OL,4,Cas chocolate and butter prices rise
OL,6,FMike Watkins, head of retailer and
OL,7,Fbusiness insight at NIQ, said: "The
OL,8,Fuptick in prices reflects several
OL,9,Ffactors: global supply costs, seasonal
OL,10,Ffood inflation driven by weather
OL,11,Fconditions, the conclusion of
OL,12,Fpromotional activity linked to recent
OL,13,Fsporting events, and a rise in
OL,14,Funderlying operational costs.
OL,16,F"As shoppers return from their summer
OL,17,Fholidays, many may need to reassess
OL,18,Fhousehold budgets in response to
OL,19,Frising household bills."
